yumCoffee

This is a project I decided to take on after I finished my first statistical computing class. I was on a coding high then, and Im 99% confident that the high is still going.

In this project, I collected my own tasting profile for coffee and decided to plot my patterns. Its funny because as I did this plotting project and as I continue to collect more data, I can see some obvious patterns in my data that I actually didnt notice of myself.

My Coffee Taste Profile

I recorded all of my preferences for all coffees that I have tried. Right now, Im still getting through two whole bean bags of Peets coffee, so I wont be able to add in new data for a while.

I put my ratings in coffee_list.csv, which you can access here. Heres a random sample of what is in coffee_list.csv.

Visualizing Coffee Preferences

Heres a plot of the coffees I have had according to roast. In this plot Special means that the coffee was not black.

Favorite Roast

Lets look at my favorite roasts! In the following plot, you can see some data points that represent where I got the coffee from, my rating, and the roast of the coffee.

This plot shows the same information above, except I labelled the points by store as opposed to coloring them by store.

I know that many statisticians hate pie charts, but you can at least admit theyre pretty.

The following calculation tells me what my favorite roasts are according to my taste profile. I dont agree with it though because I know that I really like French Roast. I just havent had enough French Roasts or had more decent Dark Roasts.

## This taster's favorite drinks have been from:
##  Special.  Dark.

Favorite Store

Heres a plot of where I bought my coffee. The overlapping text in the plot is annoying, yes, but I think its legible enough. If you cannot read what the first three labels say, here you go: Costco, Never Too Latte, and Ross.

Apparently, my favorite store to buy coffee is Costco. Im not surprised, and Im glad my membership is doing me some good.

## This taster frequently goes to: Costco.

Top 3 Coffees

Lets look at my Top 3 Coffees over time. Here we see a plot of ratings over time just to examine what kind of bias Im perpetuating as I rate the coffees I try.

Here is a density plot of the coffee ratings I gave out. We can obviously see that my ratings come from distinct distributions.

My average taste rating is 2.42. I dont think this makes me a coffee prude, nor does it justify my taste profile. I think it means that I really hate Instant Coffee, and several 0s brought down my mean score a lot.

## This taster's average rating is: 2.485294.

This says that my favorite coffees ever have been San Francisco Bay French Roast OneCup, Joes Tall Dark and Handsome, and the Pistachio Mocha Latte from Never Too Latte. I think that these are good estimates for my favorites, although I am not actually that much of a fan of super sugary drinks unless theyre boba drinks. So, I also calculated my Top 3 without Special drinks included, I would probably do analyses on Special drinks and black coffee in different sections.

## Including Special drinks, this taster's top 3 favorite drinks are:
##  French Roast OneCup.  Tall Dark and Handsome.  Pistachio Mocha Latte.
## Excluding special drinks, this taster's top 3 favorite drinks are:
##  French Roast OneCup.  Tall Dark and Handsome.  Sumatra K-Cup.
